            <div class="col-12">
              <h3><b>National Identity, Religious Identity, and Unity in Diversity</b></h3>
              <p><img src="/img/collab/collab7.jpg" alt="" style="width: 154px;float: left;margin-right: 13px;">One of problems with multicultural society is its vulnerability of intergroup prejudice and conflict. Together with <a href="http://fathalimoghaddam.com/">Fathali Moghaddam</a>  (Georgetown University) and Eko A. Meinarno (Universitas Indonesia), we are testing the relationship between National Identity, Religious Identity, and Unity in Diversity, and how it can relate to intergroup helping. The research team includes Joevarian Hudiyana (Universitas Indonesia) and <a href="https://psychology.georgetown.edu/people/phd-students">Mia Hendricks</a>  (Georgetown University).</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
